This paper deals with data science platforms and their provenance ingestion mechanisms, which are related to databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes graph query operators to manipulate the stored provenance information, which is related to graph theory and algorithms (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the evolving nature of the provenance graph and the difficulty in understanding it, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
